                     <p>
                        <placeName key="place_107027">Clapcote</placeName>.
                             
                            Indenture by which <persName>sir <forename>Edmund</forename> 
                           <surname>Rede</surname>, kt.</persName>, demises to <persName>
                           <forename>Wm</forename>. <surname>Herdewik</surname>, prior</persName> &amp;c. of <orgName key="org_107004">W<supplied>allingford</supplied>
                        </orgName>, his manors of <placeName type="manor" key="place_108053">Ruyschcourt and Clopcote</placeName> lately held by <persName>
                           <forename>Thomas</forename> 
                           <surname>Slade</surname>
                        </persName> and <persName>
                           <forename>Robert</forename> 
                           <surname>Broun</surname>
                        </persName>, with 2/- rent from an orchard and garden in <placeName key="place_107073">W<supplied>allingford</supplied>
                        </placeName> by <placeName type="street" key="place_108060">Wodestrete</placeName> on the west and <placeName type="street" key="place_108061">Lekestrete</placeName> on the east, for 99 years. Rent 40 marks. Given in the chapter-house. 
                            <origDate when="1465-12-07">7 Dec. 1465.</origDate>
                        </p>
